'''Florian Grillitsch''' (born 7 August 1995) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] or [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre back]] for Portuguese [[Primeira Liga]] club [[SC Braga|Braga]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Neunkirchen, Austria]] on 7 August 1995,<ref name="Florian Grillitsch – World Football">{{WorldFootball.net|florian-grillitsch}}</ref> Grillitsch played for SVSF Pottschach and [[SKN St. Pölten|St. Pölten]] in his youth football career.<ref name="2013–14 season">{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/florian-grillitsch/spieler/bundesliga/2024-25/tsg-hoffenheim |title=Florian Grillitsch |website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] |publisher=kicker |access-date=21 August 2015|language=de}}</ref>

===Werder Bremen===

====2013–15====
Grillitsch joined [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] on 1 July 2013. He split the 2013–14 season between the Werder Bremen U19 team and [[SV Werder Bremen II|Werder Bremen II]].<ref name="Florian Grillitsch – World Football"/> He made 15 appearances in the A-Junioren-Bundesliga Nord/Nordost scoring 11 goals<ref name="2013–14 season"/> and made five appearances in the [[Regionalliga Nord]] for Werder Bremen II.<ref name="2013–14 season"/> In the [[2014–15 Regionalliga|2014–15 season]], Grillitsch made 26 appearances scoring nine goals for Werder's reserve team.<ref name="2014–15 season">{{cite web|title=Florian Grillitsch|url=https://www.kicker.de/florian-grillitsch/spieler/bundesliga/2024-25/tsg-hoffenheim|access-date=21 August 2015|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|publisher=kicker|language=de}}</ref>

====2015–16 season====
Grillitsch made his first team debut during the [[2015–16 SV Werder Bremen season|2015–16 season]].<ref name="Florian Grillitsch » Club matches">{{cite web|title=Florian Grillitsch » Club matches|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe318201/florian-grillitsch/club-matches/|access-date=21 August 2015|publisher=World Football}}</ref> He played the full 120 minutes including extra-time in the 2–0 win against [[Würzburger Kickers]] in the first round of the [[DFB-Pokal]] on 8 August 2015, notably assisting [[Anthony Ujah]] for 1–0.<ref>{{cite news|title=Werder zieht den Kopf aus der Schlinge - dank Ujah und Bartels|url=https://www.kicker.de/wuerzburg-gegen-bremen-2015-dfb-pokal-2841071/spielbericht|access-date=21 August 2015|newspaper=kicker|date=8 August 2015|language=de}}</ref> His first [[Bundesliga]] match was a 3–0 loss to [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] on matchday one on 15 August 2015. He replaced the veteran [[Clemens Fritz]] after 70 minutes at 2–0.<ref>{{cite news|title=Choupo-Moting und Huntelaar eiskalt - Schalke siegt|url=https://www.kicker.de/bremen-gegen-schalke-2015-bundesliga-2854926/analyse|access-date=21 August 2015|newspaper=kicker|date=15 August 2015|language=de}}</ref> He also played for Werder Bremen II during the 2015–16 season.<ref name="Florian Grillitsch » Club matches"/> Grillitsch achieved his first assist in the [[Bundesliga]] as Werder beat Mainz 3–1 on 24 October 2015 setting up [[Fin Bartels]] for the third goal. He played the full 90 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bremen end losing streak with stunning six-minute spell|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/blmd10n-1-fsv-mainz-05-1-3-sv-werder-bremen-report.jsp|publisher=Bundesliga|access-date=24 October 2015|date=24 October 2015}}</ref> Four days later, Grillitsch prominently featured in Werder's 1–0 second-round DFB-Pokal victory over 1. FC Köln, providing a major goal-scoring chance for Ujah, playing multiple through-balls and almost scoring.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dorow|first1=Olaf|last2=Waterkamp|first2=Thorsten|title=Werder feiert Ujah|trans-title=Werder celebrates Ujah|url=http://www.weser-kurier.de/werder/werder-bundesliga_artikel,-Werder-feiert-Ujah-_arid,1239925.html|publisher=Weser Kurier|access-date=29 October 2015|language=de|date=28 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Die Noten: Starker Wiedwald, mutiger Grillitsch|trans-title=Grades: strong Wiedwald, courageous Grilltisch|url=http://www.kreiszeitung.de/werder-bremen/noten-werder-profis-dfb-pokal-5697845.html|publisher=Kreiszeitung Syke|access-date=29 October 2015|language=de|date=28 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Werder in Noten|trans-title=Werder grades|url=http://www.weser-kurier.de/werder/werder-fotos_galerie,-Werder-in-Noten-_mediagalid,35556.html|publisher=Weser Kurier|access-date=29 October 2015|language=de|date=28 October 2015}}</ref> Afterwards, he was voted "Man of the match" by the club's fans.<ref>{{cite web|title=Grillitsch spielt sich in den Vordergrund|url=http://www.radiobremen.de/sport/fussball/werder/grillitsch108.html|publisher=Radio Bremen|access-date=29 October 2015|language=de|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151102020702/http://www.radiobremen.de/sport/fussball/werder/grillitsch108.html|archive-date=2 November 2015}}</ref>

====2016–17 season====
On 18 March 2017, Grillitsch scored his second goal of the [[2016–17 SV Werder Bremen season|2016–17 season]] in a 3–0 win against [[RB Leipzig|Leipzig]], a match that saw all three of Werder Bremen's Austrian players score in the club's highest win of the season.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Knips|first1=Björn|title=Der Ösi-Tag: Werder feiert Kaiserschmarrn-Sieg|url=https://www.kreiszeitung.de/werder-bremen/nachbericht-werder-bremen-gegen-leipzig-oesi-tag-werder-feiert-kaiserschmarrn-sieg-7854861.html|access-date=18 March 2017|work=Kreiszeitung|date=18 March 2017|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Werder Bremen - RB Leipzig 3:0, 1. Bundesliga, Saison 2016/17, 25.Spieltag - Spielbericht|url=https://www.kicker.de/bremen-gegen-leipzig-2017-bundesliga-3317476/analyse|access-date=18 March 2017|work=kicker Online|date=18 March 2017|language=de}}</ref>

===1899 Hoffenheim===
[[file:FlorianGrillitsch.jpg|thumb|Grillitsch with Hoffenheim in May 2019]]
On 16 January 2017, Grillitsch signed a contract with [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]] until 2021, starting from the [[2017–18 TSG 1899 Hoffenheim season|2017–18 season]].<ref name="Wechsel im Sommer: Grillitsch wird Hoffenheimer">{{cite news|title=Wechsel im Sommer: Grillitsch wird Hoffenheimer|url=https://www.kicker.de/wechsel-im-sommer_grillitsch-wird-hoffenheimer-668856/artikel|access-date=17 January 2017|publisher=kicker|date=16 January 2017|language=de}}</ref>

He made his debut for the club in the league match against [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen]] (1–1 draw) on August 26, 2017. Grillitsch scored his first goal for 1899 Hoffenheim on 2 November that year in the [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] against [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|Istanbul Başakşehir]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2022091--basaksehir-vs-hoffenheim/ |title=Başakşehir 1–1 Hoffenheim |publisher=UEFA |date=2 November 2017 }}</ref> However, Hoffenheim finished last in the group behind Istanbul Başakşehir, [[SC Braga]] and [[PFK Ludogorets]].

Things went better in the [[Bundesliga]], with a fourth-place finish in 2017–18, and a group stage spot in the [[UEFA Champions League]]. The following seasons, Grillitsch finished eighth, seventh, eleventh and eighth again with Hoffenheim, in his five seasons at the club, where he clocked up 151 appearances with eight goals and eleven assists.

Grillitsch was a starter in the vast majority of those matches. But in the summer of 2022, Grillitsch let his contract expire with the club.

===Ajax and Hoffenheim again===
After moving to then Dutch champions [[AFC Ajax]] in September 2022,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://english.ajax.nl/articles/ajax-contracts-florian-grillitsch |title=Ajax contracts Florian Grillitsch |publisher=AFC Ajax |date=1 September 2022 }}</ref> Grillitsch returned to Hoffenheim after a year on a free transfer, signing a contract until 2026.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/aktuelles/news/2023/06/florian-grillitsch-kehrt-zur-tsg-hoffenheim-zurueck |title=Florian Grillitsch kehrt zur TSG Hoffenheim zurück |publisher=TSG 1899 Hoffenheim |language=de |date=27 June 2023 }}</ref>

====Loan to Valladolid====
On 3 February 2025, Grillitsch was loaned to Spanish side [[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] for the remainder of the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Florian Grillitsch para el centro del campo del Pucela |url=https://www.realvalladolid.es/noticias/florian-grillitsch-para-el-centro-del-campo-del-pucela |access-date=2025-02-03 |website=Real Valladolid |language=es}}</ref>

===Braga===
On 29 August 2025, Grillitsch signed a two-season contract with [[SC Braga|Braga]] in Portugal.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=SC Braga|url=https://scbraga.pt/florian-grillitsch-e-reforco-ate-2027/|title=Florian Grillitsch é reforço até 2027|trans-title=Florian Grillitsch is a reinforcement until 2027|date=29 August 2025|access-date=4 September 2025|language=pt}}</ref>

